	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=33114><span id= >Dread Lord Anbori</span></a><br><span id=notbold>286 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.57]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>#1 they only stack if they are named differently:<br>Example #1<br><br>Preservation of Xegony + Mana Preservation IV<br>These WILL stack, but I believe they will never be able to hit 100% mana preservation.&nbsp;&nbsp;It might just be possible that if you build up enough preservation items to save virtually 99% of mana, but I have yet to test these.<br><br>Example #2<br>Fury of Ro + Fury of E'ci + Anger of Solusek<br>I believe these will stack as well even above 100% and the Fury of (god's name here) will even stack with each other, but if you pay attention to the specifics of the focus, they are only usable against lesser, non-dragon, non-giant, non-AoE targets which rule out casting against many mobs.  But in situations such as PvP can become UNGODLY if you play on a Zek server.  Also very useful in many other cases.<br><br>Example #3<br>Affliction Haste IV + Affliction Haste III<br>I don't think these stack but I haven't yet tested these.<br><br>Example #4<br>Affliction Efficiency IV + Affliction Haste Iv<br>These do stack and can be very beneficial to casters.  This can save MASSIVE mana and downtime in many different situations.<br><br>As I don't play pure casters very often, and play hybrids more than anything, I have yet to test these out to the fullest extent.  But good luck in your testing and grouping of these focus items!<br><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=338886 target=_new> Renmazuo Skoaldiak {Tallon Zek} </a> <img src=/ubbnew/graemlins/king.gif></p>&nbsp;<br><span style='color: Maroon;'><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=338886 target=_new> Renmazuo Skoaldiak {Tallon Zek} </a> <img src=/ubbnew/graemlins/sly.gif><br>There is